# AI System Rules

This project implements an AI market intelligence platform.

All AI workflows must follow these architecture rules.

---

# AI Execution Flow

LangGraph Workflow  
↓  
Agent  
↓  
AI Runner  
↓  
Model Router  
↓  
Provider  
↓  
LLM

Agents must never call LLM providers directly.

---

# Required Infrastructure

All AI tasks must go through:

src/ai/runner/runAI.ts

which internally uses:

src/ai/router/modelRouter.ts

---

# Routing Rules

Use task-based routing:

classification → cheap model  
extraction → medium model  
reasoning → strong model  
synthesis → strong model  
validation → cheap model

---

# Provider Layer

All provider calls must go through:

src/ai/providers/

Example:

openrouter.ts

---

# Prohibited Patterns

Do not allow:

openai.chat(...)  
anthropic.messages(...)  

inside agents.

Agents must only call:

runAI(task, prompt)

---

# LangGraph Integration

All complex AI workflows must be implemented as LangGraph graphs.

Agents should remain small and composable.

---

# Observability

All AI calls should be traceable and observable.

Future integrations:

Langfuse  
ai_runs table  
evaluation datasets

---

# Future Architecture

System will later support:

- RAG retrieval
- semantic caching
- hybrid AI models
- model routing strategies
